/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51901_ShortDesc", "A hood of thick, dark material")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51901_LongDesc", "The Executioner was once a man but cursed by the gods to walk the dunes of the Exiled Lands until repentant. This never happened, and as the Executioner became more and more corrupted, he became less and less of a man, until the corruption was all that remained.\n\nThis hood has inlaid metal sheets, providing ample protection.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51903_ShortDesc", "A robe of thick, dark material")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51903_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

They dress in black robes which serve to protect them against the searing heat of the volcano where they make their home.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51904_ShortDesc", "A hood of thick, dark material")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51904_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

This hood covers the head and conceals the face, allowing the wearer to proceed with dark deeds in complete anonymity.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51905_ShortDesc", "Handwraps made of a thick, dark material")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51905_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

These handwraps provide coverage against the warmth of the volcano, while allowing the hands to remain nimble enough to work the volcanic soil that clings to the caldera.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51906_ShortDesc", "A pair of thick leather sandals")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51906_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

These sandals offer good grip on the rough stone that covers the inside of the volcano. While they are not designed to withstand the extremes of the lava flows that run along the volcano floor, they still provide some protection against the scorching heat.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51907_ShortDesc", "A skirt of thick, dark material")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51907_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They were not ghosts or phantoms. They were four tall men, with shaven, vulture-like heads, and black robes that hid their feet. Their hands were concealed by their wide sleeves.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The Votaries of Skelos are a group that believes they have stumbled upon the legendary Well of Skelos, right in the midst of the Exiled Lands. They devote their time to listening for whispers from the Well, in an attempt to further their sorcerous knowledge.

This skirt is often worn by cultists who work the volcanic soil to grow crops. The additional mobility provided by the skirt is useful for those who spend their days bending and crouching.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51995_ShortDesc", "A formal headdress worn by Jhebbal Sag priests")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51995_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Balthus saw a lean figure of middle height, almost hidden in ostrich plumes set on a harness of leather and copper. From amidst the plumes peered a hideous and malevolent face. The plumes puzzled Balthus. He knew their source lay half the width of a world to the south. They fluttered and rustled evilly as the shaman leaped and cavorted.</> - Beyond the Black River

The worship of Jhebbal Sag has long been forgotten by the civilized Hyborians, but his priests in the Black Kingdoms and Pictish wilderness still spread his religion through fear and violence.

A large part of this is the ceremonial garb that priests don for their rituals. Ornate headdresses decorated with ostrich feathers are common - even among the Picts who trade for feathers with Zingaran pirates who carry them up from the south.

Despite offering no protection, the intimidation that comes from wearing such a headdress should not be underestimated.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51996_ShortDesc", "A headpiece worn by Acolytes of Derketo")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51996_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">That's what the black people of Kush call the Apples of Derketa. Derketa is the Queen of the Dead. Drink a little of that juice, or spill it on your flesh, and you'd be dead before you could tumble to the foot of this crag.</> - Red Nails

Derketo was originally worshipped in Shem, but was quickly adopted in Stygia and the Black Kingdoms further south.

The dual nature of Derketo is death and fertility, and as such she is often paired with the most powerful deity of the kingdom she is associated with. Derketo is the consort of Set in Stygia, but the companion of Dagon in Zembabwei. In Kush she is Derketa, Queen of the Dead, and there, she walks alone.

This ceremonial armor is designed to awe and seduce in equal measure.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52001_ShortDesc", "A simple turban of hide and fiber")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52001_LongDesc", "In the Exiled Lands, the fierce sun beating down on the unprotected head can cause extreme delirium in a short amount of time.
Apart from protection from the sun, this turban offers a small amount of protection from attacks on the head.
Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.
Created from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52002_ShortDesc", "A light chestpiece of hide and fiber")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52002_LongDesc", "Designed to keep the wearer cool, this armor emphasizes movement and agility in combat over straight up protection.\nThe blow that misses is always better than the one that lands. In this case, the one that lands will cause a significant amount of damage due to the simple construction of this armor.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52003_ShortDesc", "A pair of flexible hide gauntlets")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52003_LongDesc", "Hide pieces bound to a soft underbody of cloth keep these gauntlets as flexible as possible while offering some protection from attacks.\nBlows to the hand can cause crippling injuries, particularly to archers who need to have all of their fingers intact if they are to draw a bow.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52004_ShortDesc", "A loose fitting cloth wrap, bound to the waist with rawhide thongs")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52004_LongDesc", "This wrap allows the legs to move freely, giving full range of motion. This is particularly useful to the adventurer just beginning their journey, as it allows them to make the all-important decision of fight or flight.\nLight armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52005_ShortDesc", "A pair of sturdy boots made from cloth and hide")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52005_LongDesc", "These boots of cloth wrapped and laced in hide, provide protection and warmth for the feet.\nThere are many dangers in the Exiled Lands and the small scorpions, spiders and snakes that can strike without warning are reason enough to keep legs and feet well covered.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52011_ShortDesc", "A riveted leather cap with a facemask")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52011_LongDesc", "This leather helmet includes large cheek  and neck protectors and a facemask for filtering the sand and dust from the air.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52012_ShortDesc", "Leather spaulders riveted to articulated rerebraces")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52012_LongDesc", "The fastest way to a man\'s heart, is through his armpits\' is a common expression amongst the gladiators of Argos. Chest protection is often reinforced on the upper arms and the vulnerable areas around the armpits, rather than the central chest. Every human is already born with some natural protection over their hearts namely their ribcage and breastbone.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52013_ShortDesc", "Elbow length gauntlets of riveted leather")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52013_LongDesc", "Protecting the forearms and fingers is the primary purpose of gauntlets. The loss of a hand will cripple a warrior and the loss of fingers will cripple an archer.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52014_ShortDesc", "A leather skirt that protects the upper thighs")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52014_LongDesc", "This long leather skirt is designed to protect the upper thighs from attacks while providing mobility.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52015_ShortDesc", "Calf-length riveted leather boots")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52015_LongDesc", "These boots offer good protection for the calves and feet and their sturdy construction means that they tolerate the harsh conditions for a long time.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.\nThis riveted armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52016_ShortDesc", "A helmet made of thick reptile leather")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52016_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then for the first time humans appeared: dark-skinned, hawk-faced men in copper and leather harness, bearing bows - the warriors of pre-historic Stygia.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

The overlapping scales that offer natural protection to reptiles are an excellent source of protection for humans as well. The problem is that very few reptiles give up their skins willingly, and the most fearsome crocodiles are more than a match for a poorly armed hunter.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates a balance of protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

This style of armor is common in the Black Kingdoms.")

/LongDesc:

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52021_ShortDesc", "A horned steel helmet")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52021_LongDesc", "This helmet, ornamented with a pair of horns, is designed to ward off powerful blows to the head and keep the wearer's brains on the inside of their skull.
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52022_ShortDesc", "A heavy vest that offers significant protection")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52022_LongDesc", "Designed with defence in mind, this heavy pauldron is reinforced with overlapping steel plates on the main hand. This offers optimal protection and stability mid-swing, while allowing the wearer room to breathe and remain cool.
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52023_ShortDesc", "Steel-plated gauntlets")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52023_LongDesc", "These gauntlets are adorned with overlapping plates of steel, which keeps the main hand protected while allowing full flexibility and mobility in the off-hand. 
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52024_ShortDesc", "A steel-plated skirt for protecting the upper thighs")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52024_LongDesc", "Sewn together with riveted leather and adjoined steel plates, this skirt allows free movement of the legs while in battle, while protecting the waist and upper thighs from damage.
The wide belt that encircles the waist also has the practical purpose of protecting vital organs with a thick layer of tempered metal.
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52025_ShortDesc", "Steel-plated heavy-toed boots")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52025_LongDesc", "The upper sides of these boots are covered with a layer of steel to protect against any attacks made at that vulnerable area. The feet are often overlooked as an element of protection, but as King Namedides of Aquilonia once remarked "The enemy can't run without legs!".
His infantry were well known across the world for removing the largest toes of any prisoners of war 
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52039_ShortDesc", "A steel-plated skirt for protecting the upper thighs")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52039_LongDesc", "Sewn together with riveted leather and adjoined steel plates, this skirt allows free movement of the legs while in battle, while protecting the waist and upper thighs from damage.
The wide belt that encircles the waist also has the practical purpose of protecting vital organs with a thick layer of tempered metal.
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52040_ShortDesc", "Steel-plated heavy-toed boots")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52040_LongDesc", "The upper sides of these boots are covered with a layer of steel to protect against any attacks made at that vulnerable area. The feet are often overlooked as an element of protection, but as King Namedides of Aquilonia once remarked "The enemy can't run without legs!".
His infantry were well known across the world for removing the largest toes of any prisoners of war 
The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 
This heavy armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.
")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52046_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Darfari shamans to see the dead")

Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52047_ShortDesc", "An ornate necklace of teeth over human skin")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52047_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
This chestpiece is soft and supple, which allows for great flexibility. The teeth used in the necklace appear to be crocodile teeth, taken from the great beasts that roam the Exiled Lands.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52057_ShortDesc", "Leather spaulders riveted to articulated rerebraces")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52057_LongDesc", "The fastest way to a man\'s heart, is through his armpits\' is a common expression amongst the gladiators of Argos. /ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52061_ShortDesc", "A headdress popular among Stygian nobility")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52061_LongDesc", "It is rumoured that the noble class that rules Stygia are the results of intermingling between the ancient, pre-human race that ruled Stygia and the savage humans who overthrew them. Occasionally, there are throwbacks to this ancient bloodline born among the nobles, and these half-human creatures are forced into service in the temples of Set, kept beneath the earth and away from prying eyes.

The fashions and designs of Stygia are unique amongst the races, again a side-effect of human culture crossed over with something alien.

This clothing is the type that would be worn by Stygian nobles to a feast, a festival or an orgy.")

Through the aid of these masks they can command the dead and communicate with Yog directly.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52080_ShortDesc", "For strong necks only")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52080_LongDesc", "Many a bearer have met their untimely demise by not having their hands free. One could argue that this contraption is not an improvement, since just as many have snapped their necks by simply moving their heads too quickly.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52081_ShortDesc", "A mask that filters out the sandstorm debris")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52081_LongDesc", "When the sandstorm wails across the Exiled Lands, the choices are to take cover from the scouring sands, or be blinded and eventually, killed.
This breather mask, crafted with very small slits for the eyes that keep out most of the debris while allowing visibility and a cloth mouthpiece that filters the air, allows free movement within the sandstorm.
What lies at the heart of the storm is one of the many mysteries of the Exiled Lands.
")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52092_ShortDesc", "A simple cloth binding that protects the upper body")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52092_LongDesc", "A cloth binding that has been wound around the upper body to keep everything in its place.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52094_ShortDesc", "A simple cloth wrapping that protects the groin")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52094_LongDesc", "A cloth binding that winds between the legs to keep everything in its place.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52100_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by the Witch Queen of Lemuria")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52100_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Many Lemurians escaped to the eastern coast of the Thurian Continent, which was comparatively untouched. There they were enslaved by the ancient race which already dwelt there, and their history, for thousands of years, is a history of brutal servitude.</> - The Hyborian Age

This mask was used by the Witch Queens of Lemuria to communicate with their primary deity, Dagon, before their kingdom sank into the ocean during the cataclysm.

When the Lemurians crossed into the land of the Giant-kings, they negotiated for somewhere to settle. The Witch Queen, weary of the forced exile of her people, helped the Giant-kings to forge the bracelets, originally to facilitate communication between the two races.

Later, this mask possessed the exile Razma, controlling her thoughts and forcing her to start rebuilding the palace at the heart of Xel-ha.
This is one of the artefacts required to create the keystone that can be used to remove the slave bracelet.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52101_ShortDesc", "A headress favored by Zamorian temple dancers")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52101_LongDesc", "Zamorians are known far and wide for the depth of their wickedness and thievery, but very few speak of the prowess of the temple dancers.
It is whispered that the temple girls of Yezud wear clothing such as this when they dance before the black stone spider that is their god.

For ceremonial usage, this headdress offers very little protection against sword or fang, but offers slight relief from cold, heat and stinging sand.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52102_ShortDesc", "A blouse favored by Zamorian temple dancers")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52102_LongDesc", "Zamorians are known far and wide for the depth of their wickedness and thievery, but very few speak of the prowess of the temple dancers.
The steps of the dance are unknown, but it is clear that it eases the black madness that whispers to those who find themselves in the vicinity of the awful presence of Zath, spider-god of Yezud.

For ceremonial usage, this blouse offers very little protection against sword or fang, but offers slight relief from cold, heat and stinging sand.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52111_ShortDesc", "A headdress worn by the pleasure-dancers of Derketo")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52111_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a daughter of Luxur, and before I had known fifteen summers I had been led through the temples of Derketo, the dusky goddess, and had been initiated into the mysteries.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Trained in the temples of Luxur, the dancers of Derketo are renowned for their skill in the arts of pleasure. Thought the more stringent of the Setite priests frown upon the religion of the goddess, the wisest among them know that the deity represents the dual aspects of fertility and death.

In Stygia this manifests in the bizarre pairing of the dancers and the ritualistic killings of the cult of Set.

This headdress signifies the status of the wearer as a dancer in the service of Derketo.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52112_ShortDesc", "A blouse worn by the pleasure-dancers of Derketo")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52112_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a daughter of Luxur, and before I had known fifteen summers I had been led through the temples of Derketo, the dusky goddess, and had been initiated into the mysteries.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Trained in the temples of Luxur, the dancers of Derketo are renowned for their skill in the arts of pleasure. Thought the more stringent of the Setite priests frown upon the religion of the goddess, the wisest among them know that the deity represents the dual aspects of fertility and death.

In Stygia this manifests in the bizarre pairing of the dancers and the ritualistic killings of the cult of Set.

This loose-fitting blouse is designed to accentuate rather than conceal, to titillate rather than reveal. Dancers of Derketo are aware that lust, like fear, is one of the most powerful motivators of human kind.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52113_ShortDesc", "Bracelets worn by the pleasure-dancers of Derketo")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52113_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a daughter of Luxur, and before I had known fifteen summers I had been led through the temples of Derketo, the dusky goddess, and had been initiated into the mysteries.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Trained in the temples of Luxur, the dancers of Derketo are renowned for their skill in the arts of pleasure. Thought the more stringent of the Setite priests frown upon the religion of the goddess, the wisest among them know that the deity represents the dual aspects of fertility and death.

In Stygia this manifests in the bizarre pairing of the dancers and the ritualistic killings of the cult of Set.

These bracelets jingle with every movement of the wearer - every provocative chest shake and sinuous coil of the wrist produces a golden note.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52114_ShortDesc", "A skirt worn by the pleasure-dancers of Derketo")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52114_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a daughter of Luxur, and before I had known fifteen summers I had been led through the temples of Derketo, the dusky goddess, and had been initiated into the mysteries.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Trained in the temples of Luxur, the dancers of Derketo are renowned for their skill in the arts of pleasure. Thought the more stringent of the Setite priests frown upon the religion of the goddess, the wisest among them know that the deity represents the dual aspects of fertility and death.

In Stygia this manifests in the bizarre pairing of the dancers and the ritualistic killings of the cult of Set.

Half-transparent, this skirt presents those who watch the dancers of Derketo with shadowy outlines of the flesh that lies beneath. A stirring in the blood that sets the heart to racing - and matches the step of the dancers in full flight.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52115_ShortDesc", "Anklets worn by the pleasure-dancers of Derketo")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52115_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a daughter of Luxur, and before I had known fifteen summers I had been led through the temples of Derketo, the dusky goddess, and had been initiated into the mysteries.</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

Trained in the temples of Luxur, the dancers of Derketo are renowned for their skill in the arts of pleasure. Thought the more stringent of the Setite priests frown upon the religion of the goddess, the wisest among them know that the deity represents the dual aspects of fertility and death.

In Stygia this manifests in the bizarre pairing of the dancers and the ritualistic killings of the cult of Set.

These anklets jingle with every movement of the wearer - every provocative hip-thrust and sinuous flick of the ankle produces a golden note.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52202_ShortDesc", "A tunic woven from fibrous plants")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52202_LongDesc", "When the sand whips and swirls in the wind, abrading everything in its path, even the smallest amount of protection is appreciated.\nThis tunic provides little protection from sword or fang, but it does provide slight relief from cold, heat and stinging sand.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52203_ShortDesc", "Handwraps woven from fibrous plants")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52203_LongDesc", "Digging in the gritty soil of the Exiled Lands and tearing up plants by their roots without protection is dirty, infection-prone work. \nThese handwraps provide some protection from the elements and physical attacks.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52204_ShortDesc", "Leggings woven from fibrous plants")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52204_LongDesc", "In the Hyborian age, nudity is a part of life. In warm climates, men and women go bare chested and wear flimsy clothing, slaves are clothed in whatever tatters they can find and children run naked in the streets.\nClothing, however, is a practical bulwark against the elements. And these leggings, coarse as they may be, can protect some very sensitive areas from the elements.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52205_ShortDesc", "Footwraps woven from fibrous plants")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52205_LongDesc", "The soles of these footwraps offer very poor protection from the sharp-edged stones that litter the ground of the Exiled Lands.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52212_ShortDesc", "A leather apron for smithing")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52212_LongDesc", "Across the Hyborian kingdoms and beyond, in every village in every province, the smith is a necessity in daily life. From blades to ploughsnares, blacksmiths craft the tools and weapons to feed and arm the population.\nIn every village or town, the Blacksmith is recognized by their uniform - this simple leather apron. Offering protection from errant sparks and pockets for storing small tools, this apron is as much a badge of craft as the smiths hammer or the forge itself.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52213_ShortDesc", "Thick leather gloves offering crafting protection")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52213_LongDesc", "These gloves are made of thick leather molded over a padded inside. Made to protect the hands from damage while working with dangerous crafting elements, they offer a small amount of protection in combat.\nAs a secondary usage, the heavy gloves can be donned and worn during brawls to avoid damaging the hands in combat.\nOne famous sailor, known only as Dorgan of the Python, makes a large sum of gold by fighting his way across the Vilayet sea and betting on his own fights. He claims that the gloves keep his prize possessions safe.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52221_ShortDesc", "Shemitish turban commonly worn in the meadowland cities")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52221_LongDesc", "The meadowland cities of western Shem thrive on the trade that comes with the caravans that pass into Turan and Khitai. Due to their access to these caravans, the Shemitish people often have access to the first pick of goods coming from the east - including fine silks from Khitai and brightly dyed cloth from Turan. This bounty of cloth is reflected in the loose fitting, comfortable clothing woven by the tailors of Shem.\nThis clothing is a practical bulwark against the elements but won\'t be enough to stop a blade.\n")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52222_ShortDesc", "Shemitish tunic commonly worn in the meadowland cities")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52222_LongDesc", "The meadowland cities of western Shem thrive on the trade that comes with the caravans that pass into Turan and Khitai. /ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52225_ShortDesc", "Shemitish pointy-toed shoes")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52225_LongDesc", "While these shoes are impractical for the desert, they are incredibly comfortable.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52226_ShortDesc", "A pair of Shemitish gloves")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52226_LongDesc", "The meadowland cities of western Shem thrive on the trade that comes with the caravans that pass into Turan and Khitai. /ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52293_ShortDesc", "Rough gloves suited for climbing")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52293_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">His groping hands and feet found niches and knobs, precarious holds at best, and sometimes he virtually hung by his finger nails. Yet upward he went, clawing, squirming, fighting for every foot.</> - Jewels of Gwahlur

As civilization sweeps across the barbaric nations of the world it brings comfort, security and occasionally, peace. But in such times, men forget the skills that they once had.

The ability to climb, for example, to find purchase on the steepest slopes and cling by the fingernails to the smallest of outcrops. To traverse the world using no more than the power of muscle and grit.

The barbaric Cimmerians and tribes of Afghul are known among the civilized nations for their near miraculous climbing ability. As any inhabitant of the Exiled Lands will tell you, there is no miracle here. Just the iron will to survive.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52295_ShortDesc", "Studded boots for climbing")
/LongDesc:

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52301_ShortDesc", "A simple turban of hide and fiber")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52301_LongDesc", "In the Exiled Lands, the fierce sun beating down on the unprotected head can cause extreme delirium in a short amount of time.
Apart from protection from the sun, this turban offers a small amount of protection from attacks on the head.
Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.
Created from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52302_ShortDesc", "A light chestpiece of hide and fiber")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52302_LongDesc", "Designed to keep the wearer cool, this armor emphasizes movement and agility in combat over straight up protection.\nThe blow that misses is always better than the one that lands. In this case, the one that lands will cause a significant amount of damage due to the simple construction of this armor.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52303_ShortDesc", "A pair of flexible hide gauntlets")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52303_LongDesc", "Hide pieces bound to a soft underbody of cloth keep these gauntlets as flexible as possible while offering some protection from attacks.\nBlows to the hand can cause crippling injuries, particularly to archers who need to have all of their fingers intact if they are to draw a bow.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52304_ShortDesc", "A loose fitting cloth wrap, bound to the waist with rawhide thongs")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52304_LongDesc", "This wrap allows the legs to move freely, giving full range of motion. This is particularly useful to the adventurer just beginning their journey, as it allows them to make the all-important decision of fight or flight.\nLight armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52305_ShortDesc", "A pair of sturdy boots made from cloth and hide")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52305_LongDesc", "These boots of cloth wrapped and laced in hide, provide protection and warmth for the feet.\nThere are many dangers in the Exiled Lands and the small scorpions, spiders and snakes that can strike without warning are reason enough to keep legs and feet well covered.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52306_ShortDesc", "The formal helm of a Stygian officer")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52306_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

This ornamented helm is commonly worn by officers of higher rank to make them more easily recognizable on the battlefield.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52307_ShortDesc", "A shirt of Stygian scale mail")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52307_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

Scale mail used to be reserved for the nobility, but as the kingdoms surrounding Stygia began to use more sophisticated weaponry, it was decided that the Stygian soldiers required more protection. Now scale mail has become the standard.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52308_ShortDesc", "Bracers worn by Stygian soldiers")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52308_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

These bronze bracers protect the lower arm in the clash of shields, while allowing the wearer the flexibility of wrist and hand to thrust into the gaps above and below the shield.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52309_ShortDesc", "A skirt of Stygian scale mail")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52309_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52310_ShortDesc", "Sandals worn by Stygian soldiers")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52310_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

The Stygian pike men are sometimes called hoppers by their enemies. Their insistence in wearing open soled sandals into battle means that in the clash of shield walls, enemies will often target their feet.

Stygian officers, however, consider this a boon as an enemy focused on looking down is less likely to see the pike that pierces their helmet.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52406_ShortDesc", "A helm commonly worn by Hyrkanian Raiders")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52406_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">About them and among them, like the drift of a storm, were strewn slashed and trampled bodies in steel caps and leather jerkins - archers and pikemen.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored knights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

This leather helm provides significant protection against blows to the head.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52407_ShortDesc", "A chest piece favored by Hyrkanian Raiders")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52407_LongDesc", "Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored knights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

This style of armor was reportedly created by a band of raiders who call themselves the Wolves of the Steppes. Led by the fearsome, Bhangi Khan, they have often been spotted on raids deep in the eastern empire of Khitai.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52408_ShortDesc", "Leather gauntlets favored by Hyrkanian Raiders")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52408_LongDesc", "Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored knights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

These leather gloves protect the hands in battle, while offering enough flexibility for shooting the horse-bows of the Hyrkania.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52411_ShortDesc", "A helm commonly worn by Hyrkanian Raiders")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52411_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">About them and among them, like the drift of a storm, were strewn slashed and trampled bodies in steel caps and leather jerkins - archers and pikemen.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

This leather helm provides significant protection against blows to the head.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52421_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52421_LongDesc", "Ware the dust is a common farewell among the farmers of the meadowlands of Shem. It's meaning is simple - if you see a cloud of dust from the south, then Stygian Raiders are on their way.

Though the river Styx forms the natural border between Stygia and Shem, the Stygians delight in raiding their northern neighbor for slaves and riches.

Though King Cstephon III of Stygia disavows the raiders each time, those who have observed the raids note that the raiders act with militant discipline and do not rape, and pillage as normal raiders are wont to do.

Perhaps this is why the raiders wear masks such as this. To keep their identity hidden.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52422_ShortDesc", "A chestpiece worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52422_LongDesc", "Ware the dust is a common farewell among the farmers of the meadowlands of Shem. It's meaning is simple - if you see a cloud of dust from the south, then Stygian Raiders are on their way.

Though the river Styx forms the natural border between Stygia and Shem, the Stygians delight in raiding their northern neighbor for slaves and riches.

Though King Cstephon III of Stygia disavows the raiders each time, those who have observed the raids note that the raiders act with militant discipline and do not rape, and pillage as normal raiders are wont to do.

This chestpiece offers excellent protection for the neck, shoulders and belly, while still being open enough to keep the wearer cool in the hot deserts of Stygia.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52423_ShortDesc", "Bracers worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
/LongDesc:

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52436_ShortDesc", "A horned helm worn by the Shamans of Kambuja")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52436_LongDesc", "The jungle-locked kingdom of Kambuja is mysterious to the inhabitants of the dreaming west. Unlike neighboring Vendhya, the locals do not welcome foreign trade and it is said that any merchant who sets themselves on the paths that lead into the jungle will never return.

This armor, then, is a rarity, made from a half-remembered glimpse of a Kambujan Shaman captured by the Vendhyans and put on display in the nations of the west.

The helm is more intimidating than protective, modelled on the blasphemous shapes of a heinous demonic entity. Known as Tim.")

/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52447_LongDesc", "The jungle-locked kingdom of Kambuja is mysterious to the inhabitants of the dreaming west. Unlike neighboring Vendhya, the locals do not welcome foreign trade and it is said that any merchant who sets themselves on the paths that lead into the jungle will never return.\n\nThis armor, then, is a rarity, made from a half-remembered glimpse of a Kambujan Shaman captured by the Vendhyans and put on display in the nations of the west.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52451_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by Lemurian warriors")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52451_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.\n\nThe mask can be used to hide the face of the wearer, as they plunder an enemy in the open ocean.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52452_ShortDesc", "A chestpiece worn by Lemurian warriors")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52452_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.\n\nThe chestpiece is designed to allow freedom of movement for swimming. It\'s not as light as some other armors, but it is not going to drag a warrior down into the depths. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52453_ShortDesc", "Gauntlets worn by Lemurian warriors")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52453_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.\n\nThese gauntlets are designed to protect the hands and lower arms, but the hands are freed to take up the work of the sailor.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52454_ShortDesc", "A tasset worn by Lemurian warriors")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52454_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.

This tasset is designed to be quickly kicked off if a warrior falls into water, freeing the warrior from its protection and weight before they are sucked into the depths.

The metal discs sewn on to this garment depict Dagon, the god of the Lemurians.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52455_ShortDesc", "Boots worn by Lemurian warriors")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52455_LongDesc", "The Lemurians were a nautical people before their islands sank beneath the waves during the cataclysm, and this armor reflects those cultural values.\n\nThese boots protect the lower part of the leg and foot, while offering a simple mechanism for quick release in the event that the warrior needs to be barefoot in a hurry.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52466_ShortDesc", "Ornate jewelry designed for Lemurian royalty")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52466_LongDesc", "The rulers of ancient Lemuria were, without exception, women. They worshipped Dagon and any male heirs to the throne were given in sacrifice to the Demon of the Depths.\n\nThe royal garments are therefore designed to be worn by their Witch Queens. Which explains their femininity, if not exactly why some men insist on wearing them.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52467_ShortDesc", "An ornate gown designed for Lemurian royalty")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52467_LongDesc", "The rulers of ancient Lemuria were, without exception, women. They worshipped Dagon and any male heirs to the throne were given in sacrifice to the Demon of the Depths.

The royal garments are therefore designed to be worn by their Witch Queens. Which explains their femininity, if not exactly why some men insist on wearing them.

It is clear that the designers of the royal Lemurian clothing were also responsible for the design of the bracelet that imprisons people in the Exiled Lands. Another mystery.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52494_ShortDesc", "A replacement prosthetic for a hand")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52494_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.\n\nWho needs dual-wielding anyway?")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52495_ShortDesc", "A wooden prosthetic leg")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52495_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.\n\nSomehow, this peg leg allows the temporary removal of your own - where it is stored is anyones guess.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52496_ShortDesc", "A pair of earrings worn by buccaneers")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52496_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.\n\nThese earrings are crude, cobbled together from base metals. But among pirates, keeping up a certain appearance is all the matters. Like the Black Hand, however, it seems to work.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52497_ShortDesc", "A replacement prosthetic for a hand")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52497_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. /ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52498_ShortDesc", "A wooden prosthetic leg")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52498_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.\n\nSomehow, this peg leg allows the temporary removal of your own - where it is stored is anyones guess.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52499_ShortDesc", "A heavily stitched pair of boots")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52499_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.

These boots are a reflection of their attitude, a patchwork of sloppy stitching and flung together pieces. Like the Black Hand, however, it seems to work.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements that balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52500_ShortDesc", "A crudely-fashioned eye patch")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52500_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52501_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by devotees of Set")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52501_LongDesc", "The dispassionate features of the serpent have been modeled and refined in this mask. It distorts the features of the wearer and brings them closer to the cold beauty of the serpents so beloved of their god.\nUsed primarily in rituals within the temple of Set, this mask nevertheless offers a certain level of protection for the face of the wearer.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52502_ShortDesc", "A choker worn by devotees of Set")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52502_LongDesc", "Crafted from the finest golds, this garment is light and supple. It molds pleasingly to the form and accentuates the chest. The mysteries of Set are not all blood and death - the ritual that depicts the coupling of Set with his mistress, Derketo, has been described by Mitrean scholars as \"a blasphemous orgy of wine and blood.\" Though they always take the opportunity to vist any temple of Derketo during such rites. For the purposes of research, of course.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52504_ShortDesc", "A shendyt worn by devotees of Set")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52504_LongDesc", "Woven silk edged with golden trim has been used to shape this ornamental shendyt. Worn by devotees of Set during their rituals, these shendyts are often stained in the blood of sacrifice.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52505_ShortDesc", "A pair of sandals worn by devotees of Set")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52505_LongDesc", "These ceremonial sandals were not designed for the harsh environment of the desert, but rather the stone floors of the temple. Runnng in sand wearing these is an uncomfortable experience and fighting in them is almost impossible due to poor balance.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52509_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Yoggite warriors")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52509_LongDesc", "Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, Darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52510_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Yoggite warriors")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52510_LongDesc", "Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, Darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52511_ShortDesc", "A ritual mask used by Yoggite shamans to see the dead")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52511_LongDesc", "Carved into solid wood and decorated with intricate symbols, the watcher mask is said to remove the veil between the wearer and the spiritual world where Yog dwells.
Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, Darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.
")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52512_ShortDesc", "An ornate necklace of teeth over human skin")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52512_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
This chestpiece is soft and supple, which allows for great flexibility. The teeth used in the necklace appear to be crocodile teeth, taken from the great beasts that roam the Exiled Lands.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52513_ShortDesc", "Bracers of blood-dyed leather")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52513_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These bracers are the color of blood and made of a soft leather wrapped with cloth. A close look reveals human molars dangling from the bindings on the gauntlets.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52514_ShortDesc", "Skirt of human skin")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52514_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These skirt is simple and adorned with a belt of small beads and human bones and teeth.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52515_ShortDesc", "Ankle wraps of soft leather")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52515_LongDesc", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These leather wraps, generously called greaves, are supple leather adorned with human bones and teeth.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52516_ShortDesc", "A helmet crafted from the skull of Hyena")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52516_LongDesc", "The Dogs of the Desert are a mysterious clan who inhabit the northern reaches of the desert. Their obsession with capturing and taming Hyenas and their fanatical worship of the god known as Jhebbal Sag keeps them aloof from the other factions in the region.\nThe fact that they wear uncured furs and unclean bones probably doesn\'t help.\nSome might question wearing fur in the warmth of the desert, but nights can be brutally cold and the slopes of the mountain are not that far to the north.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52517_ShortDesc", "A chestpiece crafted from the fur of Hyenas")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52517_LongDesc", "The Dogs of the Desert are a mysterious clan who inhabit the northern reaches of the desert. Their obsession with capturing and taming Hyenas and their fanatical worship of the god known as Jhebbal Sag keeps them aloof from the other factions in the region.\nThe fact that they wear uncured furs and unclean bones probably doesn\'t help.\nSome might question wearing fur in the warmth of the desert, but nights can be brutally cold and the slopes of the mountain are not that far to the north.")

/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52518_LongDesc", "The Dogs of the Desert are a mysterious clan who inhabit the northern reaches of the desert. Their obsession with capturing and taming Hyenas and their fanatical worship of the god known as Jhebbal Sag keeps them aloof from the other factions in the region.\nThe fact that they wear uncured furs and unclean bones probably doesn\'t help.\nSome might question wearing fur in the warmth of the desert, but nights can be brutally cold and the slopes of the mountain are not that far to the north.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52519_ShortDesc", "A wrap crafted from the fur of Hyenas")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52519_LongDesc", "The Dogs of the Desert are a mysterious clan who inhabit the northern reaches of the desert. Their obsession with capturing and taming Hyenas and their fanatical worship of the god known as Jhebbal Sag keeps them aloof from the other factions in the region.\nThe fact that they wear uncured furs and unclean bones probably doesn\'t help.\nSome might question wearing fur in the warmth of the desert, but nights can be brutally cold and the slopes of the mountain are not that far to the north.")

/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52522_LongDesc", "Followers of Mitra commit to a life of simplicty and dignity. They prefer knowledge to ritual and the calm of meditation to the storm of battle.\nThis tunic reflects the simple principles of the Mitraen devout.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52526_ShortDesc", "A turban designed to protect the head from the elements")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52526_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

This turban has been refined in the time that they have spent in the Exiled Lands, offering comfort against the warm weather of the region and limited protection against the scouring sands.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52527_ShortDesc", "A loose shirt favoured by relic hunters")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52527_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

Still scavengers at heart, this shirt is paired with a small leather sack for storing any treasure that a relic hunter might stumble across while exploring the Exiled Lands.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52528_ShortDesc", "A set of sturdy gloves for handling relics")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52528_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

Too many foolish souls have lost life, limb and sanity to the effects of handling the relics of the ancient world. These gloves were created with to deal with that specific problem of adventuring.

Sturdy enough to protect the wrists and hands against hidden needles or snakebites, durable enough to protect the skin against corrosive magics and sudden fires and comfortable enough to wear while jamming a hand into a sarcophagus.

They aren't particularly good against sharp weapons, however.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52529_ShortDesc", "Practical canvas pants for exploring")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52529_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

The Relic Hunters of the Exiled Lands are a curious mix of mercenaries, thieves and desperate fools. They were the original group in the Exiled Lands, exhorted to come in search of great treasures in the ruins that dot the area.

The price of their admission was to wear a bracelet that ensured they could not run off with the treasures that they found.

These pants, made of sturdy canvas, will keep the legs protected against stinging sands while allowing full freedom to leap over traps, canyons and short enemies.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52530_ShortDesc", "A set of boots design for exploring ruins")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52530_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was a far traveler and had looted the treasures of many kingdoms. But now he hesitated and shuddered before the highest adventure and the mightiest treasure of all.</> - Black Colossus

When the Relic Hunters first arrived in the Exiled Lands, they were given sandals and flat-soled shoes. It is not known how many Relic Hunters died with their toes wedged into a gap between flagstones while an ancient horror bore down upon their prone body.

Since those early days, the Relic Hunters have moved to a style of boot favoured in Shem - curled toes to avoid catching on cracks when sprinting, supple leather to allow maximum freedom of movement and high cuffs to tuck into pants and prevent the accumulation of sand.

They aren't particularly good against sharp weapons, however.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52532_ShortDesc", "A patchwork vest of leather, rope and cloth")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52532_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.

This garment, favored by the sailors of the Black Hand looks as though it has been mended so many times that none of the original material is left. Still due to the age of the garment and the many layers it exhibits more durability than it's frail appearance would indicate. 

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements that balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52534_ShortDesc", "A heavily stitched pair of leather pants")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52534_LongDesc", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.

These trousers are a reflection of their attitude, a patchwork of sloppy stitching and flung together pieces. Like the Black Hand, however, it seems to work.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements that balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52556_ShortDesc", "A helmet forged from mysterious star metal")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52556_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Free my hands and I'll varnish this floor with your brains!</> - The Scarlet Citadel

This heavy helmet is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52557_ShortDesc", "A chestpiece forged from mysterious star metal")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52557_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then, as the white stars glimmered through the blue velvet dusk, making her whirling body a blur of ivory fire, with a wild cry she threw herself at Conan's feet, and the blind flood of the Cimmerian's desire swept all else away as he crushed her panting form against the black plates of his corseleted breast.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

This impossibly hard pauldron is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52558_ShortDesc", "Gauntlets forged from mysterious star metal")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52558_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The four men wheeled at the sound and drew their swords, gaping at the mailed giant who faced them, sword in hand.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These impossibly hard gauntlets are made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52559_ShortDesc", "Leg armor forged from mysterious star metal")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52559_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He was far inferior in size and strength to the giant Cimmerian, but he was in full armor, and was famed in all the western nations as a swordsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This impossibly hard leg armor is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52560_ShortDesc", "Plated boots are forged from mysterious star metal")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52560_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They gave tongue like wolves and surged about the lone figure in the gray mail, and the clamor and din of steel drowned the cries of the circling raven.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These impossibly hard plated boots are made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52561_ShortDesc", "A helmet of hardened steel")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52561_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The plain swam to Conan's gaze, the sunlight was a thick red haze and he reeled in his saddle, grasping the flowing mane with his hand. Blood rained on his mail, but grimly he urged the stallion on.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This heavy helmet is wrought from hardened steel, the work of an advanced smith.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility.

Those who know the riddle of steel know techniques to harden steel in order to create armor of unusual resilience.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52562_ShortDesc", "A chestpiece of hardened steel")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_52562_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A gray sky arched overhead, and a moaning wind was chill with a promise of winter. Brown leaves fluttered slowly down from the bare branches, sifting upon his mailed shoulders.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility.

Those who know the riddle of steel know techniques to harden steel in order to create armor of unusual resilience.")

These heavy gauntlets are wrought from hardened steel, the work of an advanced smith.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility.

Those who know the riddle of steel know techniques to harden steel in order to create armor of unusual resilience.")

/LongDesc:
