/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91250_ShortDesc", "A plumed helmet favoured by the guardsmen of Aquilonia")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91250_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot. The clearly recognizable plume of the helmet also serves to identify guardsmen on sight - a boon for which the pickpockets of Tarantia are eternally grateful.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91251_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot.

The large pauldron on the right shoulder is designed to protect the main arm during combat, while keeping the armor flexible and relatively light.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91252_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

 The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot. 

The left bracer is stiff leather to protect the freehand, while the right is a more flexible form of padding - allowing greater blade manoeuvrability during combat.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91253_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A dully glinting, mail-clad figure moved out of the shadows into the starlight. This was no plumed and burnished palace guardsman.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot. 

Aquilonian guardsmen are often forced to chase down criminals or leap across rooftops in pursuit of fleeing foes. This short skirt is designed to allow them this freedom of movement, while still protecting their upper thighs.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

The common guardsmen of Aquilonia are some of the best equipped warriors in the world. Full plate would be impractical for their daily duties, but this armor represents a compromise between the demands of protection and the ability to perform regular patrols on foot. 

The distinctive sound of these sandals slapping against the paving stones is a hallmark of Aquilonian cities. 

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements - metal rivets, articulated leather, and fur-trimmed cloth - to balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91260_ShortDesc", "A helmet designed to intimidate")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91260_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

The helmets of Hyperboreans are designed to protect them from magical threats, as well as mundane. The witch-men of Hyperborea do not want anybody controlling their servants.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91261_ShortDesc", "A waistguard designed to intimidate")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91261_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

It is considered a challenge among Hyperborean slavers to go bare-chested on their raids, wearing nothing more than this waistguard. While it offers less protection than steel leggings and a breastplate, it intimidates newly caught slaves into submission.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91262_ShortDesc", "A set of sturdy bracers")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91262_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame - for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

Hyperborean slavers wear this armor to intimidate their enemies and cow their slaves.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91263_ShortDesc", "A loincloth worn beneath by Hyperborean slavers")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91263_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame -- for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

Primarily worn beneath the more armored waistguard, this loincloth is designed to keep the vitals of a slaver warm and protected when on long raids in the northern lands of Asgard and Vanaheim.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91264_ShortDesc", "Sturdy boots worn by Hyperborean slavers")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91264_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">There was a giant Hyperborean renegade, taciturn, dangerous, with a broadsword strapped to his gaunt frame - for men wore steel openly in the Maul.</> - The Tower of the Elephant

In the far north, east of the lands of the Nordheimers, live the tall, gaunt people known as the Hyperboreans. Ruled by the White Hand, a cabal of sorcerers, they often stage raids into Cimmeria to take slaves for their sorcerous experiments.

These boots are designed to be sturdy enough to last long trips and to grip well on rough terrain. It might be coincidental, but the additional grip makes it that much harder for a chained slave to pull a slaver off their feet.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91265_ShortDesc", "A helm commonly worn by Hyrkanian Raiders")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91265_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">About them and among them, like the drift of a storm, were strewn slashed and trampled bodies in steel caps and leather jerkins - archers and pikemen.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored knights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

This leather helm provides significant protection against blows to the head.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91266_ShortDesc", "A chest piece favored by Hyrkanian Raiders")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91266_LongDesc", "Heavy armor is generally made of iron or steel and extremely heavy. The stables of the western kingdoms breed ever larger warhorses to compensate for the increasing load of the heavily armored knights.

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

This style of armor was reportedly created by a band of raiders who call themselves the Wolves of the Steppes. Led by the fearsome, Bhangi Khan, they have often been spotted on raids deep in the eastern empire of Khitai.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91267_ShortDesc", "Leather gauntlets favored by Hyrkanian Raiders")
/LongDesc:

Not so the Hyrkanians, who rely on their sturdy steppe-bred mounts to remain swift and mobile at all times. This armor, made of overlapping sheets of leather, is designed to give the wearer as much protection as possible, while still not weighing down the rider and the mount.

These leather gloves protect the hands in battle, while offering enough flexibility for shooting the horse-bows of the Hyrkania.")

/LongDesc:

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91270_ShortDesc", "A helmet forged from mysterious star metal")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91270_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Free my hands and I'll varnish this floor with your brains!</> - The Scarlet Citadel

This heavy helmet is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91271_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then, as the white stars glimmered through the blue velvet dusk, making her whirling body a blur of ivory fire, with a wild cry she threw herself at Conan's feet, and the blind flood of the Cimmerian's desire swept all else away as he crushed her panting form against the black plates of his corseleted breast.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

/LongDesc:

/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91274_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">They gave tongue like wolves and surged about the lone figure in the gray mail, and the clamor and din of steel drowned the cries of the circling raven.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These impossibly hard plated boots are made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Armor made from this material is of a preternatural aegis.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91275_ShortDesc", "The formal helm of a Stygian officer")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91275_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

This ornamented helm is commonly worn by officers of higher rank to make them more easily recognizable on the battlefield.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91276_ShortDesc", "A shirt of Stygian scale mail")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91276_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

Scale mail used to be reserved for the nobility, but as the kingdoms surrounding Stygia began to use more sophisticated weaponry, it was decided that the Stygian soldiers required more protection. Now scale mail has become the standard.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91277_ShortDesc", "Bracers worn by Stygian soldiers")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91277_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

These bronze bracers protect the lower arm in the clash of shields, while allowing the wearer the flexibility of wrist and hand to thrust into the gaps above and below the shield.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91278_ShortDesc", "A skirt of Stygian scale mail")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91278_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

Scale mail used to be reserved for the nobility, but as the kingdoms surrounding Stygia began to use more sophisticated weaponry, it was decided that the Stygian soldiers required more protection. Now scale mail has become the standard.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91279_ShortDesc", "Sandals worn by Stygian soldiers")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91279_LongDesc", "When the armies of Stygia march, it is an impressive sight. In the vanguard, bow-wielding nobles riding bronze-worked chariots drawn by black horses and behind them, the glittering columns of mail-clad warriors.

The Stygian pike men are sometimes called hoppers by their enemies. Their insistence in wearing open soled sandals into battle means that in the clash of shield walls, enemies will often target their feet.

Stygian officers, however, consider this a boon as an enemy focused on looking down is less likely to see the pike that pierces their helmet.

The pinnacle of protection, heavy armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91280_ShortDesc", "A helmet made of thick reptile leather")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91280_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then for the first time humans appeared: dark-skinned, hawk-faced men in copper and leather harness, bearing bows - the warriors of pre-historic Stygia.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

The overlapping scales that offer natural protection to reptiles are an excellent source of protection for humans as well. The problem is that very few reptiles give up their skins willingly, and the most fearsome crocodiles are more than a match for a poorly armed hunter.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates a balance of protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

This style of armor is common in the Black Kingdoms.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91295_ShortDesc", "A helmet crafted from the skull of Hyena")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91295_LongDesc", "The Dogs of the Desert are a mysterious clan who inhabit the northern reaches of the desert. Their obsession with capturing and taming Hyenas and their fanatical worship of the god known as Jhebbal Sag keeps them aloof from the other factions in the region.\nThe fact that they wear uncured furs and unclean bones probably doesn\'t help.\nSome might question wearing fur in the warmth of the desert, but nights can be brutally cold and the slopes of the mountain are not that far to the north.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91312_ShortDesc", "An armor of old Vanir design")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91312_LongDesc", "This armor is of Vanir design and thus, protects against colder climates. In addition, the armor scraps used to build this armor have been infused by the magic and craftsmanship of the Giant Kings which bestows additional properties. This piece of armor grants an increase to Grit.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91315_ShortDesc", "This is the true power of the Warmaker\'s Champion")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91315_LongDesc", "Crafted by infusing the rusty pieces of the Warmaker\'s armor with an assortment of magical ingredients, this armor is the pinnacle of heavy armors. It withstands an enormous amount of punishment. The magical energies that surge through this helmet grant additional Grit and also functions as a breathing mask.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91317_ShortDesc", "This is the true power of the Warmaker\'s Champion")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91317_LongDesc", "Crafted by infusing the rusty pieces of the Warmaker\'s armor with an assortment of magical ingredients, this armor is the pinnacle of heavy armors. It withstands an enormous amount of punishment. The magical energies that surge through these gauntlets grant additional Strength.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91320_ShortDesc", "An ancient helmet with a ghastly aura")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91320_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It is sorcery - grisly black magic from the grim youth of the world. An awful shape has risen out of the shades of the Past, and none can stand before it.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This eldritch helm bears markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper the names Deathbringer, Kinscourge, and Maimer.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91321_ShortDesc", "An ancient chestpiece with a ghastly aura")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91321_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I have lain in your arms, panting with the violence of our love; you have held and crushed and conquered me, drawing my soul to your lips with the fierceness of your bruising kisses. My heart is welded to your heart, my soul is part of your soul! Were I still in death and you fighting for life, I would come back to the abyss to aid you--aye, whether my spirit floated with the purple sails on the crystal sea of paradise, or writhed in the molten flames of hell! I am yours, and all the gods and all their eternities shall not sever us!</> - Queen of the Black Coast

This eldritch chest armor bears markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper the names Tyros and Telith.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91322_ShortDesc", "Ancient gauntlets with a ghastly aura")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91322_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Those eyes grew and became gigantic, and in them the Cimmerian glimpsed the reality of all the abysmal and blasphemous horrors that lurk in the outer darkness of formless voids and nighted gulfs.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

These eldritch gauntlets bear markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper of the hybrid half-child of the humans and the Giant-kings.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91323_ShortDesc", "Ancient leg armor with a ghastly aura")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91323_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Wits and swords are as straws against the wisdom of the Darkness...</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

This eldritch leg armor bears markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper the names Klael the Warmaker, The Archivist, and the Priestking.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91324_ShortDesc", "Ancient plated boots with a ghastly aura")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_91324_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">By Crom, I do not like this place, where dead men rise, and sleeping men vanish into the bellies of shadows!</> - Xuthal of the Dusk

These eldritch boots bear markings and script so old no living scholar could decipher them.

The pinnacle of protection, steel armor is a solid wall of defense against any type of attack, but the extreme weight requirements mean that the wearer must sacrifice mobility. 

The strange metal of this primordial armor always carries an unholy chill, even in the noonday sun. When donning this wicked carapace, the wearer hears whispering voices, voices that tell an ancient tragedy - voices that whisper the name of the Witch Queen.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92000_ShortDesc", "A helmet made of thick reptile leather")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92000_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then for the first time humans appeared: dark-skinned, hawk-faced men in copper and leather harness, bearing bows - the warriors of pre-historic Stygia.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

The overlapping scales that offer natural protection to reptiles are an excellent source of protection for humans as well. The problem is that very few reptiles give up their skins willingly, and the most fearsome crocodiles are more than a match for a poorly armed hunter.

Offering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates a balance of protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.

This style of armor is common in the Black Kingdoms.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92010_ShortDesc", "A helmet made of thick reptile leather")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92010_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He plunged through the undergrowth, hip-deep in the marshes; dived headlong into the deep water, heedless of sharks or crocodiles, and swam to the galley and was clambering up the chain on to the deck, dripping and exultant, before the watch saw him.</> - The hour of the Dragon

Only the chosen of Sobek are allowed to wear this armor. The scales themselves are thicker than regular crocodile scales, and it has been further reinforced by star metal plates. As a result, the armor is much heavier than normal medium armor but offers additional protection.

This armor does not grant any bonus to heat or cold-protection.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92102_ShortDesc", "Shemitish tunic commonly worn in the meadowland cities")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92102_LongDesc", "Made from the finest silks, this armor has been reinforced while still retaining its weight. The craftsmanship is nothing less than magnificent.")

/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92103_LongDesc", "Made from the finest silks, this armor has been reinforced while still retaining its weight. The craftsmanship is nothing less than magnificent.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92104_ShortDesc", "A pair of pants worn by Zingaran Freebooters")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92104_LongDesc", "Enchanted, or perhaps corrupted, by the presence of the Winged Death, these pants have been infused with unholy magic, granting the wearer additional attribute enhancements.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92105_ShortDesc", "A pair of boots worn by Zingaran Freebooters")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92106_ShortDesc", "A crudely-fashioned eye patch")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92106_LongDesc", "Sought after by the Vanir as a holy relic of the gods, this Eye-patch may blind one eye but grants terrific strength in return.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92107_ShortDesc", "A horned steel helmet")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92107_LongDesc", "An incredibly durable helmet made from the finest materials.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92108_ShortDesc", "A mask worn by Stygian soldiers on raids")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92108_LongDesc", "Wrested from the clutches of the undead in the Unnamed City, this old Stygian helmet has seen better days but even though it is old, the craftsmanship still shines through.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92110_ShortDesc", "A plumed helmet favoured by the guardsmen of Aquilonia")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92110_LongDesc", "This helmet protects against gas and sandstorms alike.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92111_ShortDesc", "A leather vest and pauldron in Aquilonian style")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92111_LongDesc", "Magnificent in its make and a sight feared by anyone that opposes the glory of the Aquilonian legions.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92112_ShortDesc", "A helmet forged from mysterious star metal")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92112_LongDesc", "This helmet seems to have more padding than armor, resulting in a helmet that is extremely warm.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92113_ShortDesc", "Plated boots are forged from mysterious star metal")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92113_LongDesc", "Lined with the fur of mammoths, these boots are warm and comfortable and their grip allows the wearer to carry weight more reliably.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92114_ShortDesc", "A helmet made of thick reptile leather")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92114_LongDesc", "This helm grants the wearer a bonus to their strength.")

/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92115_LongDesc", "These gauntlets grant the wearer a bonus to their grit.")

/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92116_LongDesc", "Crafted from the scales of the Red Mother, this helmet grants an inordinate amount of cold protection.")

/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92136_LongDesc", "An ancient armor piece worn by the most competent and feared Aesir warrior in the Exiled Lands. This armor is the greatest accomplishment of a fabled blacksmith named Thorgar of the North.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92200_ShortDesc", "A helm worn by the Khari Overseers")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92200_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world. The job of managing the slave legion fell to the overseers, a hard-hearted lot tasked with the messy business of motivating human chattle to serve, fight for, and often die in service of their masters. \n\nThis open-faced light helm offers moderate protection against blows - but shields the wearer from direct sunlight and hateful glances from the enslaved. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92201_ShortDesc", "Shoulder and upper-chest protection worn by the Khari Overseers")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92201_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world. The job of managing the slave legion fell to the overseers, a hard-hearted lot tasked with the messy business of motivating human chattle to serve, fight for, and often die in service of their masters. \n\nIn hot, arid climates, the mantle offers a modicum of chest and shoulder protection without the enclosing the wearer -- like an extremely small poncho.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92202_ShortDesc", "Ornamental bracers worn by Khari Overseers")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92202_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world. The job of managing the slave legion fell to the overseers, a hard-hearted lot tasked with the messy business of motivating human chattle to serve, fight for, and often die in service of their masters. \n\nThese largely decorative bracers offer only the slightest hint at actual protection, but look good doing it.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92203_ShortDesc", "A leather skirt that protects the upper thighs of the Overseers")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92203_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world. The job of managing the slave legion fell to the overseers, a hard-hearted lot tasked with the messy business of motivating human chattle to serve, fight for, and often die in service of their masters. \n\nThis knee-length leather skirt is designed to protect the upper thighs from attacks without impeding mobility.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92204_ShortDesc", "Sandals worn by the Khari Overseers")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92204_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world. The job of managing the slave legion fell to the overseers, a hard-hearted lot tasked with the messy business of motivating human chattle to serve, fight for, and often die in service of their masters. \n\nThese sandals lace along the length of the calf, allowing the wearer freedom of movement while protecting the front of the leg. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92205_ShortDesc", "A light helmet designed to intimidate.")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92205_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world. The role of maintaining a steady supply to the Khari slave markets fell to the Raider crews, a villainous corps of black-souled reavers with a reputation for unmatched cruelty. 

Sightings of the snake-headed prows of the Khari Raider crews often meant mothers would slay their weak or enfeebled children rather than see them suffer at the hands of the pitiless slavers.  

This leather helm and mask combination provides moderate protection to the head, but are primarily designed to project fear and intimidation.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92206_ShortDesc", "A chestguard made in the style of the Khari")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92206_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world. The role of maintaining a steady supply to the Khari slave markets fell to the Raider crews, a villainous corps of black-souled reavers with a reputation for unmatched cruelty. 

Sightings of the snake-headed prows of the Khari Raider crews often meant mothers would slay their weak or enfeebled children rather than see them suffer at the hands of the pitiless slavers.  

The remarkable weave of this dark copper mail chestpiece offers excellent protection for the neck, shoulders and belly, without trapping heat. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92207_ShortDesc", "Bracers worn by Khari Raiders. ")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92207_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world. These bracers protect the forearm and can be used to deflect superficial blows, thus keeping the wearer swinging and fighting just a little longer. ")

/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92209_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world. The role of maintaining a steady supply to the Khari slave markets fell to the Raider crews, a villainous corps of black-souled reavers with a reputation for unmatched cruelty. 

Sightings of the snake-headed prows of the Khari Raider crews often meant mothers would slay their weak or enfeebled children rather than see them suffer at the hands of the pitiless slavers.  

These sandals lace along the length of the calf, allowing the wearer freedom of movement while protecting the front of the leg. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92210_ShortDesc", "A Helm worn by Khari soldiers in the field.")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92210_LongDesc", "As masters of the slave trade, the strength and backbone of the Khari empire was the vast body of thralls captured from across the known world.  

While many of the slave legions were used as expendable fodder, those demonstrating exceptional dedication or performance in the field could earn a kind of freedom with promotion to the regular infantry ranks. Historians believe that a cadre of these 'free-men soldiers,' possibly even Lemurian exiles, were involved with sparking the rebellion that led to the eventual decline and dissolution of the Khari empire.  

Like the Khari Overseer and Raider headpieces, the Soldier's helm was designed for intimidation first and protection second. Still, the hardened segmented armour offers excellent defense against slashing and piercing attacks.")
